description:
World's Most Dangerous Roads Series 2

Travel Documentary hosted by Adrian Dunbar, published by BBC in 2012 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

World's Most Dangerous Roads Series 2
Pairs of celebrities on terrifying car journeys: as the first series showed, it's a formula with a happy mix of jokes and jeopardy. Thanks to all your comments for the first Series, we decided to present you the second part of Most Dangerous Roads In The World. Mostly it includes the roads that you have suggested as well as other well known and popular dangerous roads. Have a great time checking these!




2)  Ho Chi Minh Trail 
Sue Perkins and Liza Tarbuck drive the legendary Ho Chi Minh Trail, a network of dangerous roads hacked through mountains and jungles of Laos and Vietnam. Its role in the Vietnam War has left it one of the most perilous roads in the world as it is littered with unexploded bombs. Sue and Liza face a gruelling drive to some of the least explored sections of the trail, with both terrifying and hilarious consequences.



